cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.AL, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with online algorithms for broadcast scheduling, which involves managing requests for pages of information at a server. This topic is closely related to data structures (cs.DS) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also involves analysis of algorithms (cs.AL) and information theory (cs.IT) in order to determine the competitiveness of the longest-wait-first algorithm. Finally, the paper discusses the extension of the algorithm to more general objective functions, which could fall under game theory (cs.GT).
